{
  "stem": "21482.5",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--to tell me about a trick that was being played.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oskar Schindler had, you know, some of our young boys working for him.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And one of them was a wonderful-- well, he could make false papers.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He could falsify paper.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So among other-- all kinds of papers, he would falsify orders for food, for equipment.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he-- they had the pads, and you have to make the stamps and everything.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Well, one day they made orders for SS [INAUDIBLE] Leopold, and that he had to go back to Berlin for his-- Hitler wanted to give him some orders.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he left.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he left just when the war was ending, so that when-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] so once he would go to Berlin, there was no way of him to come back.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We-- I guess Oskar Schindler knew that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So when the war was ending, and when Oskar Schindler called us to the factory to announce that the war had-- was going to end at midnight-- and we listened to the broadcast from-- the BBC broadcast by Winston Churchill-- when he turns to the guards and told them, you can either become war criminals or you can return home to your families, there was nobody to tell them not to.",
      "word_count": 71
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They left.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because who knows.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "If, you know, Leopold would still be there, he would probably want to kill us.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because the Germans were killing the Jews till the very last moment.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "As the Allies were coming through the front gate, they were killing the Jews in the back.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it was different because [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] we had less, you know.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had much less food, but we still had-- we still were together with the same people.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
